name: 'A La Mode'
description:
The light entered where the roses’ thorn had slid my skin

It’s fascinating to see how much we can own, without having 

How much we can desire, without satisfaction 

How much we can tire ourselves in search for inner peace 

The storms we create to conquer, so we can die as heroes

The pain we allow ourselves to feel, 

so we can finally see... 

the beauty


@Alexander Koning - The Poetic Pirates Society
